
1. Lock is initialized when it hits the endpoint for the first time. Creates lock_id and stores it internally.
1. To update the phone and email, user can go to website with lock_id in url (ex. www.tracelock.com/23412341623784asdfre) where a form will be
3. When lock is unlocked, it sends another request to the endpoint, updating its location
4. When lock is broken, hits endpoint, which will alert the user and start showing the devices gps coords, and path that it has taken on website
5. When lock is running low on battery, will hit endpoint to alert user


Optionally, could include weather data and time when lock is broken which would allow us to do basic analytics on when
locks are more likely to be broken into.


